.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::RelayAdmin \- NIP\-86 relay management API
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 3
\&    use Net::Nostr::RelayAdmin qw(
\&        encode_request decode_response request_with_auth
\&    );
\&
\&    # Encode a management request
\&    my $body = encode_request(
\&        method => \*(Aqbanpubkey\*(Aq,
\&        params => [\*(Aqaa\*(Aq x 32, \*(Aqspammer\*(Aq],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Decode a response
\&    my $result = decode_response(\*(Aq{"result":true}\*(Aq);
\&    # or handle errors
\&    eval { decode_response(\*(Aq{"error":"not authorized"}\*(Aq) };
\&    warn $@ if $@;
\&
\&    # Build a full authenticated request
\&    my %req = request_with_auth(
\&        method    => \*(Aqsupportedmethods\*(Aq,
\&        params    => [],
\&        key       => $key,
\&        relay_url => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&    # %req contains: body, authorization, content_type
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements the client side of the NIP\-86 relay management API. NIP\-86
defines a JSON\-RPC\-like request\-response protocol over HTTP for relay
administration. Requests are sent to the relay\*(Aqs WebSocket URI with
\&\f(CW\*(C`Content\-Type: application/nostr+json+rpc\*(C'\fR and authorized using
NIP\-98 HTTP auth with a required \f(CW\*(C`payload\*(C'\fR tag.
.PP
The following management methods are defined by NIP\-86:
.ie n .IP """supportedmethods"" \- list supported methods" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWsupportedmethods\fR \- list supported methods" 4
.IX Item "supportedmethods - list supported methods"
.PD 0
.ie n .IP """banpubkey"", ""unbanpubkey"", ""listbannedpubkeys"" \- pubkey banning" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWbanpubkey\fR, \f(CWunbanpubkey\fR, \f(CWlistbannedpubkeys\fR \- pubkey banning" 4
.IX Item "banpubkey, unbanpubkey, listbannedpubkeys - pubkey banning"
.ie n .IP """allowpubkey"", ""unallowpubkey"", ""listallowedpubkeys"" \- pubkey allowlisting" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWallowpubkey\fR, \f(CWunallowpubkey\fR, \f(CWlistallowedpubkeys\fR \- pubkey allowlisting" 4
.IX Item "allowpubkey, unallowpubkey, listallowedpubkeys - pubkey allowlisting"
.ie n .IP """listeventsneedingmoderation"", ""allowevent"", ""banevent"", ""listbannedevents"" \- event moderation" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWlisteventsneedingmoderation\fR, \f(CWallowevent\fR, \f(CWbanevent\fR, \f(CWlistbannedevents\fR \- event moderation" 4
.IX Item "listeventsneedingmoderation, allowevent, banevent, listbannedevents - event moderation"
.ie n .IP """changerelayname"", ""changerelaydescription"", ""changerelayicon"" \- relay metadata" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWchangerelayname\fR, \f(CWchangerelaydescription\fR, \f(CWchangerelayicon\fR \- relay metadata" 4
.IX Item "changerelayname, changerelaydescription, changerelayicon - relay metadata"
.ie n .IP """allowkind"", ""disallowkind"", ""listallowedkinds"" \- kind filtering" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWallowkind\fR, \f(CWdisallowkind\fR, \f(CWlistallowedkinds\fR \- kind filtering" 4
.IX Item "allowkind, disallowkind, listallowedkinds - kind filtering"
.ie n .IP """blockip"", ""unblockip"", ""listblockedips"" \- IP blocking" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWblockip\fR, \f(CWunblockip\fR, \f(CWlistblockedips\fR \- IP blocking" 4
.IX Item "blockip, unblockip, listblockedips - IP blocking"
.PD
.PP
Unknown method names are passed through without parameter validation,
allowing forward compatibility with relay\-specific extensions.
.SH FUNCTIONS
.IX Header "FUNCTIONS"
All functions are exportable. None are exported by default.
.SS encode_request
.IX Subsection "encode_request"
.Vb 4
\&    my $body = encode_request(
\&        method => $method_name,
\&        params => \e@params,       # optional, defaults to []
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Encodes a relay management request as a JSON string with \f(CW\*(C`method\*(C'\fR
and \f(CW\*(C`params\*(C'\fR fields. Croaks if \f(CW\*(C`method\*(C'\fR is missing or empty.
Croaks if \f(CW\*(C`params\*(C'\fR is provided but not an array reference.
.PP
For known NIP\-86 methods, validates that params contain the correct
types: 64\-char lowercase hex for pubkey/event\-id methods, non\-negative
integers for kind methods, non\-empty strings for relay metadata
methods, and non\-empty strings for IP methods.
.PP
.Vb 4
\&    my $body = encode_request(
\&        method => \*(Aqbanpubkey\*(Aq,
\&        params => [\*(Aqaa\*(Aq x 32, \*(Aqspammer\*(Aq],
\&    );
.Ve
.SS decode_response
.IX Subsection "decode_response"
.Vb 1
\&    my $result = decode_response($json);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a JSON response string and returns the \f(CW\*(C`result\*(C'\fR field. If
the response contains a non\-empty \f(CW\*(C`error\*(C'\fR field, croaks with the
error message. Croaks if the input is missing, empty, or not valid
JSON.
.PP
.Vb 1
\&    my $result = decode_response(\*(Aq{"result":true}\*(Aq);
\&
\&    eval { decode_response(\*(Aq{"error":"not authorized"}\*(Aq) };
\&    if ($@) {
\&        # handle error
\&    }
.Ve
.SS request_with_auth
.IX Subsection "request_with_auth"
.Vb 6
\&    my %req = request_with_auth(
\&        method    => $method_name,
\&        params    => \e@params,       # optional, defaults to []
\&        key       => $nostr_key,
\&        relay_url => $relay_url,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Builds a complete authenticated relay management request. Returns
a hash with three keys:
.ie n .IP """body"" \- the JSON request body" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWbody\fR \- the JSON request body" 4
.IX Item "body - the JSON request body"
.PD 0
.ie n .IP """authorization"" \- a NIP\-98 ""Authorization"" header value (""Nostr <base64>"")" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWauthorization\fR \- a NIP\-98 \f(CWAuthorization\fR header value (\f(CWNostr <base64>\fR)" 4
.IX Item "authorization - a NIP-98 Authorization header value (Nostr <base64>)"
.ie n .IP """content_type"" \- ""application/nostr+json+rpc""" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWcontent_type\fR \- \f(CWapplication/nostr+json+rpc\fR" 4
.IX Item "content_type - application/nostr+json+rpc"
.PD
.PP
The NIP\-98 auth event uses \f(CW\*(C`POST\*(C'\fR as the HTTP method, the
\&\f(CW\*(C`relay_url\*(C'\fR as the \f(CW\*(C`u\*(C'\fR tag, and includes a \f(CW\*(C`payload\*(C'\fR tag with
the SHA\-256 hash of the request body, as required by NIP\-86.
.PP
Croaks if \f(CW\*(C`key\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`relay_url\*(C'\fR is missing. The \f(CW\*(C`key\*(C'\fR must be a
Net::Nostr::Key object with a private key for signing.
.PP
.Vb 6
\&    my %req = request_with_auth(
\&        method    => \*(Aqsupportedmethods\*(Aq,
\&        params    => [],
\&        key       => $key,
\&        relay_url => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
